UK expresses " great respect " for new HK governor . Britain on Wednesday welcomed the choice of shipping magnate Tung Chee - hwa as Hong Kong ' s new leader - in - waiting and said it had " great respect " for him . A 400 - strong selection committee , carefully assembled by Beijing , voted overwhelmingly as expected for the 59 - year - old businessman to take over when the British colony reverts to Chinese rule next year . Prime Minister John Major and Foreign Secretary Malcolm Rifkind both sent messages of congratulation to Tung and said he was most welcome to visit Britain whenever he wanted . " We have great respect for him . British ministers have every confidence he will be a worthy first chief executive of Hong Kong ' s special administrative region , " a foreign office spokesman said . 
